        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 4 at 2:04PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 156 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking showers and thunderstorms
along a line extending from west of Helena across Canyon Ferry Lake
to the Bridger Range. Movement was north at 35 mph. Expect a period
of rain and gusty winds to around 40 mph as this area of
precipitation arrives with isolated stronger thunderstorm cells
producing lightning  with perhaps some small hail over the
mountains. This area of precipitation will as far north as areas
from Lincoln east to Wolf Creek and the Little Belts by 3 PM.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Helena, Townsend, White Sulphur Springs, East Helena, Montana City,
Wolf Creek, Fort Logan On The Smith River, York, Rimini, Alhambra,
Spring Meadow Lake State Park, Austin, Fort Logan, Winston, Maudlow,
Silos, Clancy, Checkerboard, Goose Bay, and Ringling.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
